richard alexander fownes (born 26 october 1983) is a musician from brighton, england. he currently plays and writes for bad for lazarus and with scissors. he also plays live for unkle. he joined the eighties matchbox b-line disaster after andy huxley's departure in 2005, but in 2008 he left to join nine inch nails. however this plan collapsed and he was replaced with justin meldal-johnsen.